# Migration steps — from OpenMTR → OpenMTR2

Follow these steps in order to stand up the new repo and push it to GitHub.

---

## 1. Create the new GitHub repo

Go to https://github.com/new and create:
- Name: `OpenMTR2`
- Description: OpenMTR — modern Qt6 network diagnostic tool (clean fork)
- Public
- No README, no .gitignore (we supply our own)

---

## 2. Clone your existing OpenMTR locally (if not already)

```
git clone https://github.com/x-rated/OpenMTR.git
```

---

## 3. Clone White-Tiger/WinMTR for its src/ files

```
git clone https://github.com/White-Tiger/WinMTR.git winmtr-redux-temp
```

---

## 4. Set up the OpenMTR2 folder

```
mkdir OpenMTR2
cd OpenMTR2
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/x-rated/OpenMTR2.git
```

---

## 5. Copy all files from OpenMTR into OpenMTR2 root

Copy these files from OpenMTR/:
- MainWindow.cpp
- MainWindow.h
- WinMTRNetWrapper.h
- CrashHandler.h
- main.cpp
- resources.qrc
- app.rc
- app.ico
- check.svg
- app.manifest
- LICENSE
- engine/   (entire folder)

---

## 6. Copy the supplied scaffold files into OpenMTR2

These are the files generated for this repo:
- README.md
- .gitignore
- OpenMTR2.sln
- OpenMTR2.vcxproj
- .github/workflows/build.yml
- engine/winmtr-redux/ATTRIBUTION.md

---

## 7. Copy White-Tiger/WinMTR src/ into engine/winmtr-redux/

```
cp winmtr-redux-temp/src/* OpenMTR2/engine/winmtr-redux/
```

The files there are reference-only and are NOT added to the .vcxproj compile list.

---

## 8. Rename references inside MainWindow.cpp and main.cpp

Do a find-and-replace:
- `"OpenMTR v1.0.0"` → `"OpenMTR v2.0.0"` (or keep v1.0.0 — your call)
- Window title string in setWindowTitle() calls

The .vcxproj already outputs `OpenMTR2.exe`. Once you rename the repo to
`OpenMTR` you can rename the .sln/.vcxproj back to `OpenMTR`.

---

## 9. First commit and push

```
cd OpenMTR2
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit — OpenMTR2 with Qt6 UI + WinMTR-refresh engine + WinMTR Redux reference"
git push -u origin main
```

---

## 10. Verify GitHub Actions

Go to https://github.com/x-rated/OpenMTR2/actions — the build job should
trigger automatically and produce an `OpenMTR2-x64` artifact within ~5 minutes.

---

## 11. Later: rename and archive

Once OpenMTR2 is stable:
1. Archive `x-rated/OpenMTR` (Settings → Archive repository)
2. Rename `x-rated/OpenMTR2` → `OpenMTR` (Settings → Repository name)
3. Update README and any external links

---

## Notes

- The `engine/winmtr-redux/` files are GPL-2.0, same as this project.
  ATTRIBUTION.md inside that folder documents the origin.
- The active engine is `engine/*.ixx` (WinMTR-refresh by leeter) — the
  winmtr-redux files are not compiled.
- To create a tagged release: `git tag v2.0.0 && git push origin v2.0.0`
  The CI `release` job will auto-run and create a GitHub Release with a zip.
